To invoke a web service using Jolie definitions generated by wsdl2jolie, you need to create an instance of the generated Jolie service and call its methods corresponding to the web service operations. Here's a general syntax:

1. Import the required libraries and load the WSDL file using wsdl2jolie:
```java
import jolie.lang.*;
import org.w3c.dom.*;

public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
    JolieFactory factory = new JolieFactory();
    DocumentBuilderFactory dbFactory = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
    Document doc = dbFactory.newDocumentBuilder().parse(new File("wsdl_file.wsdl"));
    // ...
  }
}
```

2. Create a Jolie service instance:
```java
JolieService service = factory.load("path/to/generated/jolie/service.jolie");
```
3. Call the web service operation using the generated interface:
```java
JolieServicePort port = service.getPort("port_name", "binding_name");
JolieRequest request = factory.newRequest();
// Set request parameters if needed
JolieResponse response = port.call(request);
// Process the response
```

